ttp://gismoldova.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/09139ac36f8943529cef2e00f802c3fc mobile version]).[[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)|Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova]].\n* [http://logos.press.md/1321_kalak/ \u0410\u041e \u00ab\u042d\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0437\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u00ab\u041b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441-\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441\u00bb \u2116 11 (1321) 27 \u041c\u0430\u0440. 2020 \"\u0412\u0441\u044f \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043e COVID-19\"]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Moldova]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Moldova]]\n[[Category:2020 in Moldova|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Moldova}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Moldova\n| map1            = [[File:Republic of Moldova Map of the regions affected by COVID-19.svg|250px]]\n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Moldova|Republic of Moldova]]\n| first_case      = [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]\n| arrival_date    = 7 March 2020 <ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-07_Press release_2\"/><br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month=03|day=07|year=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 2,472 <ref name=\"MSMPS_Press releases\">{{cite web |title=Press releases of the Minister of Health, Labor and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/advanced-page-type/comunicate-de-presa |website=msmps.gov.md}}</ref><ref name=\"gismoldova\">{{cite web |title=COVID-19 \u00een Republica Moldova: situa\u0163ia la zi |url=http://gismoldova.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/d274da857ed345efa66e1fbc959b021b |website=gismoldova.maps.arcgis.com}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = 457 <ref name=\"MSMPS_Press releases\"/><ref name=\"gismoldova\"/>\n| deaths          = 67 <ref name=\"MSMPS_Press releases\"/><ref name=\"gismoldova\"/>\n| active_cases    = 1,948\n| suspected_cases = 63 <ref name=\"MSMPS_Press releases\"/><ref name=\"gismoldova\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [https://ansp.md/index.php/category/actualizarea-situatiei-privind-coronavirus/ National Agency for Public Health: epidemiological situation related to COVID-19]\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Moldova|the Republic of Moldova]] on 7 March 2020. Data on cases presented in this article refers to the entire territory of the Republic of Moldova, including the [[Transnistria autonomous territorial unit|Transnistrian region]], which is currently not controlled by the constitutional authorities of the Republic of Moldova.\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" />\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Moldova medical cases chart}}\n\n=== Before 24 February 2020 ===\n* '''27 January 2020''': the Minister of Health, Labor and Social Protection Mrs. [[Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu]] convened an extended meeting of the Commission for Exceptional Situations and Public Health Emergencies of the Ministry of Health, Labor and Social Protection. This meeting was also attended by representatives of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and European Integration, the Ministry of Internal Affairs, the Ministry of Finance, the General Inspectorate of Border Police, the Customs Service, the National Insurance Company in Medicine, the National Food Safety Agency and the National Agency for Public Health. Participants discussed the measures to prevent and control the infection with the new type Coronavirus (2019-nCov), based on the epidemiological situation and the global spread of the infection.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-01-27_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title=Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu a convocat \u0219edin\u021ba Comisiei pentru Situa\u021bii excep\u021bionale \u0219i urgen\u021be de s\u0103n\u0103tate public\u0103 cu privire la m\u0103surile de prevenire \u0219i control a infec\u021biei cu Coronavirusul de tip nou |trans-title=Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu convened the Commission for Exceptional Situations and Public Health Emergencies regarding the measures to prevent and control the infection with the new type Coronavirus |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/viorica-dumbraveanu-convocat-sedinta-comisiei-pentru-situatii-exceptionale-si-urgente-de |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=11 April 2020 |language=ro |date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* '''2 February 2020''': the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health was convened by the [[Prime Minister of Moldova|Prime Minister]] Mr. Ion Chicu.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ion Chicu a convocat \u0219edin\u021ba Comisiei na\u021bionale extraordinar\u0103 de s\u0103n\u0103tate public\u0103 |trans-title=Ion Chicu convened the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health |url=https://gov.md/ro/content/ion-chicu-convocat-sedinta-comisiei-nationale-extraordinara-de-sanatate-publica |website=gov.md |publisher=Government of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=29 March 2020 |language=ro |date=29 March 2020}}</ref> The Commission has examined the information presented by the Ministry of Health, Labor and Social Protection and found that the epidemiological situation related to the infection with the novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV) is tense, which has led the [[World Health Organization]] to declare a Public Health Emergency of International Concern. The Commission adopted the Decision No. 1 which provides, ''inter alia'', that risk assessment for public health will continue to be carried out with the attribution, if necessary, of the alert code resulting from the epidemiological situation related to the infection with the new Coronavirus (2019-nCoV).<ref name=\"Gov_Cornavirus_info\">{{cite web |title=Informa\u021bii privind Coronavirus |trans-title=Information regarding the Coronavirus |url=https://gov.md/ro/content/informatii-privind-coronavirus |website=gov.md |publisher=Government of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=29 March 2020 |language=ro |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''18 February 2020''': the National Agency for Public Health received from Germany, with the support of the World Health Organization, test kits to detect the virus that causes COVID-19.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-02-18_Press release\">{{cite web |title=Testele pentru depistarea Coronavirusul de tip nou au ajuns \u00een Republica Moldova |trans-title=The tests for the detection of new Coronavirus have arrived in the Republic of Moldova |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/testele-pentru-depistarea-coronavirusul-de-tip-nou-au-ajuns-republica-moldova |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=11 April 2020 |language=ro |date=18 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Recep\u0163ionarea kiturilor pentru depistarea Coronavirusului de tip nou (SARS-CoV-2) |trans-title=Receiving kits for the detection of the new Coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2) |url=https://ansp.md/index.php/receptionarea-kiturilor-pentru-depistarea-coronavirusului-de-tip-nou-sars-cov-2/ |website=ansp.md |publisher=National Agency for Public Health |accessdate=11 April 2020 |language=ro |date=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Code yellow alert (24 February \u2013 7 March 2020) ===\n* '''24 February 2020''': the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health was convened by the Prime-minister Mr. Ion Chicu.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ion Chicu a convocat Comisia na\u021bional\u0103 extraordinar\u0103 de s\u0103n\u0103tate public\u0103 |trans-title=Ion Chicu convened the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health |url=https://gov.md/ro/content/ion-chicu-convocat-comisia-nationala-extraordinara-de-sanatate-publica |website=gov.md |publisher=Government of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=29 March 2020 |language=ro |date=29 March 2020}}</ref> The Commission adopted the Decision No. 2 which provides, ''inter alia'', the establishment of the Code Yellow alert at national level in the context of the epidemiological situation related to COVID-19 infection and consideting the possible risk for a public health emergency.<ref name=\"Gov_Cornavirus_info\"/><ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-02-24_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title=Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu: \"\u00cendemn popula\u021bia s\u0103 manifeste maxim\u0103 responsabilitate \u0219i s\u0103 respecte toate m\u0103surile de igien\u0103 \u0219i precau\u021bie pentru a preveni \u00eemboln\u0103virea cu Coronavirus de tip nou\" |trans-title=Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu: \"I urge the population to show maximum responsibility and to respect all the hygiene and precautionary measures to prevent illness with the new type Coronavirus\" |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/viorica-dumbraveanu-indemn-populatia-sa-manifeste-maxima-responsabilitate-si-sa-respecte |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=29 March 2020 |language=ro |date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''25 February 2020''': the Republic of Moldova has put into action some anti-coronavirus measures.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dulgher |first1=Maria |title=Moldova prepares for an outbreak of coronavirus in the country |url=https://www.moldova.org/en/moldova-prepares-for-an-outbreak-of-coronavirus-in-the-country/ |website=moldova.org |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== The first case (7 March 2020) ===\nThe first coronavirus case in the Republic of Moldova was announced on 7 March 2020. The infected person is a 48-year-old woman who had returned to Moldova from Italy with the flight Milano-Chisinau. She had been taken to hospital immediately from the plane, being in a serious condition: bilateral bronchopneumonia, acute respiratory failure, fever, cough, general weakness. She suffers from a few chronical illnesses: diabetes, overweight and hypertension.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-07_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title=MSMPS confirm\u0103 primul caz de Coronavirus de tip nou \u00een Republica Moldova |trans-title=MSMPS confirms first new-type coronavirus case in the Republic of Moldova |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/msmps-confirma-primul-caz-de-coronavirus-de-tip-nou-republica-moldova |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=[[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)]] |accessdate=8 March 2020 |language=ro |date=7 March 2020}}</ref> According to the [[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)|Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of Moldova]], she was diagnosed with bilateral bronchopneumonia, fever and cough on 4 March in Italy. She was prescribed antibiotic treatment at home and put in home quarantine pending confirmation of a new type of coronavirus infection, but she decided to return to Moldova.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-08_Press release_1\">{{cite web |title=\u00cen Republica Moldova a fost confirmat primul caz de coronavirus. Se iau m\u0103suri pentru limitarea r\u0103sp\u00e2ndirii virusului |trans-title=The first case of coronavirus in the Republic of Moldova has been confirmed. Measures are put into action to limit the spread of the virus|url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/republica-moldova-fost-confirmat-primul-caz-de-coronavirus-se-iau-masuri-pentru-limitarea |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=[[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)]] |accessdate=8 March 2020 |language=ro |date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Code orange alert (8\u201312 March 2020) ===\n* '''8 March 2020''': the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health established the Code Orange alert at national level in the context of the epidemiological situation related to COVID-19 infection.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-08_Press release_1\"/>\n* '''10 March 2020''': the Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of Moldova confirmed another two cases (the 2nd and the 3rd) of coronavirus. The infected people are a woman and a man, both of them returned from Italy, on 26 February and 1 March, respectively.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-10_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title=Alte dou\u0103 cazuri de \u00eemboln\u0103viri cu infec\u021bia Coronovirus de tip nou, pe teritoriul \u021b\u0103rii. Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu \u00eendeamn\u0103 cet\u0103\u021benii s\u0103 respecte recomand\u0103rile autorit\u0103\u021bilor |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/alte-doua-cazuri-de-imbolnaviri-cu-infectia-coronovirus-de-tip-nou-pe-teritoriul-tarii |trans-title=Another two cases of a new-type coronavirus in a country. Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu urges citizens to respect the guidelines of authorities |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=[[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)]] |accessdate=10 March 2020 |language=ro |date=10 March 2020}}</ref> On the same day all foreigners coming from the countries affected by coronavirus have been banned from entering Moldova by plane.<ref>{{cite web |title=Moldova bans foreigners on all flights from countries with coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-moldova/moldova-bans-foreigners-on-all-flights-from-countries-with-coronavirus-idUSL8N2B31TO |website=reuters.com |publisher=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=11 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''11 March 2020''': the 4th case has been confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ultima or\u0103: \u00cenc\u0103 un caz de coronavirus a fost confirmat; Bilan\u021bul ajunge la 4 persoane |url=https://unimedia.info/ro/news/8610206333c068f1/inca-un-caz-de-coronavirus-a-fost-confirmat-bilantul-ajunge-la-4-persoane.html |website=unimedia.info |publisher=Unimedia |accessdate=12 March 2020 |language=ro |date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Government announced that it closing all kindergartens, schools, colleges and universities for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web |title=Moldova closes schools, universities to prevent virus spread |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-moldova/moldova-closes-schools-universities-to-prevent-virus-spread-idUSKBN20Y0VP |website=reuters.com |publisher=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=11 March 2020 |date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''12 March 2020''': 2 new cases (the 5th and the 6th) were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ultima or\u0103! \u00cenc\u0103 dou\u0103 cazuri de coronavirus, confirmate. Bilan\u021bul \u00een Moldova ajunge la 6 persoane |url=https://unimedia.info/ro/news/7a1773abb3054813/ultima-ora-inca-doua-cazuri-de-coronavirus-confirmate-bilantul-in-moldova-ajunge-la-6-persoane.html |website=unimedia.info |publisher=Unimedia |accessdate=12 March 2020 |language=ro |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> As per 12 March 2020, there were no confirmed cases in the Transnistrian region,<ref>{{cite web |title=\u041c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f, \u0432 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0443 \u043d\u0435 \u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c. \u0423\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043c \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d |url=https://tv.pgtrk.ru/ru/news/20200312/92516 |website=pgtrk.ru |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=ru |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> but 8 people were quarantined after returning from abroad.<ref>{{cite web |title=8 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0435. \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0438 \u041f\u0440\u0438\u0434\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435 |url=https://tv.pgtrk.ru/ru/news/20200311/92503 |website=pgtrk.ru |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=ru |date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Code red alert (13\u201316 March 2020) ===\n* '''13 March 2020''': the Extraordinary National Commission of Public Health established the Code Red alert at national level in the context of the epidemiological situation related to COVID-19 infection.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-13_Press release_4\">{{cite web |title=A fost instituit cod ro\u0219u de alert\u0103 \u00een leg\u0103tur\u0103 cu evolu\u021bia situa\u021biei epidemiologice privind infec\u021bia cu Coronavirusul de tip nou pe teritoriul Republicii Moldova |trans-title=A Code Red alert was established in relation to the evolution of the epidemiological situation regarding the infection with the new Coronavirus on the territory of the Republic of Moldova |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/fost-instituit-cod-rosu-de-alerta-legatura-cu-evolutia-situatiei-epidemiologice-privind |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=ro |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> During this day other 2 new cases (the 7th and the 8th) have been confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Actualizat pe 13 martie 2020 |url=https://ansp.md/index.php/actualizat-pe-13-martie-2020/ |website=ansp.md |publisher=National Agency for Public Health of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=13 March 2020 |language=ro |date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''14 March 2020''': 4 new cases were confirmed. Thus, the total number of infected people reached 12.<ref>{{cite web |title=Situa\u021bia epidemiologic\u0103 prin infec\u021bia cu Coronavirusul de tip nou (COVID-19), actualizat pe 14 martie 2020 |trans-title=Epidemiological situation related to the infection with the novel Coronavirus (COVID-19), updated on 14 March 2020 |url=https://ansp.md/index.php/actualizat-pe-14-martie-2020/ |website=ansp.md |publisher=National Agency for Public Health of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=ro |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''15 March 2020''': 11 new cases were confirmed. The total number of infected people reached 23.<ref>{{cite web |title=Date actualizate cu privire la r\u0103sp\u00e2ndirea noului tip de Coronavirus (COVID-19) \u00een Republica Moldova \u0219i recomand\u0103ri pentru popula\u021bie |trans-title=Updated information related to the spread of the novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) in the Republic of Moldova and recommendations for the population |url=https://ansp.md/index.php/date-actualizate-cu-privire-la-raspandirea-noului-tip-de-coronavirus-covid-19-in-republica-moldova-si-recomandari-pentru-populatie/ |website=ansp.md |publisher=National Agency for Public Health of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=15 March 2020 |language=ro |date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''16 March 2020''': 6 new cases were confirmed. The total number is 29. One woman recovered.\n\n=== State of emergency (since 17 March 2020) ===\n* '''17 March 2020''': the Parliament declared the state of emergency for the entire territory of the Republic of Moldova for a period of 60 days (17 March - 15 May 2020).<ref>{{cite web |title=Parlamentul a declarat stare de urgen\u021b\u0103 pe perioada 17 martie \u2013 15 mai 2020 |trans-title=The Parliament declared the state of emergency for the period 17 March - 15 May 2020 |url=http://parlament.md/Actualitate/Noutati/tabid/89/NewsId/2374/language/ro-RO/Default.aspx |website=parlament.md |publisher=Parliament of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=ro |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> During 17 March 2020, the 30th case has been confirmed.\n* '''18 March 2020''': the first death was confirmed, a 61-year-old woman who had travelled to Italy.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-18_Press release_1\">{{cite web |title=Republica Moldova a \u00eenregistrat primul deces cauzat de noul coronavirus |trans-title=The Republic of Moldova registered the first death from the new coronavirus |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/republica-moldova-inregistrat-primul-deces-cauzat-de-noul-coronavirus |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=18 March 2020 |language=ro |date=18 March 2020}}</ref> Another 6 new cases of infection have been confirmed.\n* '''19 March 2020''': 13 new cases were confirmed. The total number of infected people since 7 March 2020 reached 49.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-19_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title=\u00cen Republica Moldova sunt \u00eenregistrate 49 cazuri de infec\u021bie cu COVID-19. Respecta\u021bi recomand\u0103rile autorit\u0103\u021bilor. Sta\u021bi acas\u0103 |trans-title=The Republic of Moldova registered 49 cases of infections with COVID-19. Please respect the recommendations of authorities. Stay home |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/republica-moldova-sunt-inregistrate-49-cazuri-de-infectie-cu-covid-19-respectati |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=19 March 2020 |language=ro |date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''20 March 2020''': 17 new cases were confirmed, and the total number of infected people since 7 March 2020 reached 66.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-20_Press release_3\">{{cite web |title= 17 cazuri de COVID-19 confirmate \u00een ultimele 24 de ore |trans-title=17 cases of COVID-19 confirmed during the last 24 hours |url=http://ms.gov.md/ro/content/17-cazuri-de-covid-19-confirmate-ultimele-24-de-ore |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=ro |date=20 March 2020}}</ref> Upon the request of MoH, based on WHO Moldova recommendations short-list, Trimetrica LLC /www.trimetrica.com/ (ESRI Partner in Moldova) launched the customized ArcGIS Dashboard (an online platform) - allowing the real-time monitoring of COVID-19 cases in the Republic of Moldova. It's updated for 2 times per day.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-20_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title= O nou\u0103 platform\u0103 lansat\u0103 \u00een Moldova permite monitorizarea cazurilor de COVID-19 \u00een timp real |trans-title=A new platform launched in Moldova allows real-time monitoring of COVID-19 cases |url=https://msmps.gov.md/en/node/11175 |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=20 March 2020 |language=ro |date=20 March 2020}}</ref> The platform is accessible at this link: [http://gismoldova.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/d274da857ed345efa66e1fbc959b021b gismoldova.maps.arcgis.com]\n* '''21 March 2020''': 14 new cases were confirmed, the total number of infected people since 7 March 2020 reaching 80. Out of these 14 new cases, 2 cases were recorded for the first time in the Transnistrian region. At the same time, it was announced that the first person infected and confirmed in the Republic of Moldova (on 7 March 2020), was treated and transferred to another section for recovery against other chronic diseases. Thus, the number of recovered persons reached 2.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-21_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title= 14 cazuri noi de infec\u021bie prin COVID-19 \u00een Republica Moldova. Respecta\u021bi recomand\u0103rile medicilor. Sta\u021bi acas\u0103 |trans-title=14 new cases of infections with COVID-19. Please respect the recommendations of doctors. Stay home |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/14-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-prin-covid-19-republica-moldova-respectati-recomandarile-medicilor |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=ro |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''27 March 2020''': the second death was confirmed, a 79 years old woman who was a doctor working at the Emergency Medical Assistance Service. She got sick on 19 March, and on 24 March she was admitted to the Republican Clinical Hospital, in serious condition. The patient suffered from several chronic diseases (diabetes, heart failure, high blood pressure).<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-27_Press release_1\">{{cite web |title= Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu: \"\u00cen urm\u0103toarea perioad\u0103 depinde de noi, \u00eentreaga societate, cum vom dep\u0103\u0219i provocarea epidemiei COVID-19. Fac apel la responsabilitate\" |trans-title=Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu: \u201cIn the next period, it is up to us, the whole society, how we will overcome the challenge of the COVID-19 epidemic. I call for responsibility\u201d |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/viorica-dumbraveanu-urmatoarea-perioada-depinde-de-noi-intreaga-societate-cum-vom-depasi |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ro |date=27 March 2020}}</ref> During 27 March 2020, 22 new cases were confirmed, the total number of infected people since 7 March 2020 reaching 199. On the same day, 3 patients recovered, the total number of recoveries reaching 5.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-27_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title= Situa\u021bia epidemiologic\u0103 prin infec\u021bia COVID-19, 27 martie, ora 18.00 |trans-title=Epidemiological situation regarding the COVID-19 infection, 27 March, 18:00 |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/situatia-epidemiologica-prin-infectia-covid-19-27-martie-ora-1800 |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=ro |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''29 March 2020''': the third death was confirmed, a woman from the Transnistrian region.<ref name=\"UNIMEDIA_2020-03-31_Ultima_ora_inca_doua_decese\">{{cite web |title= Ultim\u0103 or\u0103! \u00cenc\u0103 dou\u0103 decese din cauza coronavirusului, confirmate \u00een Republica Moldova |trans-title=Breaking news! Two more deaths due to coronavirus, confirmed in the Republic of Moldova |url=https://unimedia.info/ro/news/6b1cfa6d4c5df8ea/ultima-ora-inca-un-deces-din-cauza-coronavirusului.html |website=unimedia.info |publisher=UNIMEDIA |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=ro |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-31_Press release_2\">{{cite web |title= 55 cazuri noi de infec\u021bie cu noul tip de Coronavirus, \u00een ultimele 24 de ore |trans-title=55 new cases of infection with the new type of Coronavirus, in the last 24 hours |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/55-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-cu-noul-tip-de-coronavirus-ultimele-24-de-ore |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=ro |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''31 March 2020''': after 280 tests were performed, a record number of 55 new cases were confirmed, of which 48 cases were with local transmission, while 7 were import cases (of which 6 were from the United Kingdom and 1 from Austria). Thus, the total number of infected persons since 7 March 2020 reached 353. At the same time, 4 patients were treated and discharged from hospitals, the total number of recoveries reaching 22. Also, during 31 March 2020 the fourth death was confirmed, a man from the Briceni District of the Republic of Moldova.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-03-31_Press release_2\"/>\n* '''1 April 2020''': the fifth death was confirmed, a person from the Transnistrian region.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-04-01_Press release_4\">{{cite web |title=70 cazuri noi de infec\u021bie cu noul tip de Coronavirus, \u00een ultimele 24 de ore |trans-title=70 new cases of infection with the new type of Coronavirus, in the last 24 hours |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/70-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-cu-noul-tip-de-coronavirus-ultimele-24-de-ore |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=ro |date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n* '''2 April 2020''': the sixth death was confirmed, a 53-year-old person from \u0218tefan Vod\u0103 District, which was hospitalized in a hospital from Chi\u0219in\u0103u. The patient also suffered from other chronic diseases.<ref name=\"MSMPS_2020-04-02_Press release_3\">{{cite web |title= Situa\u021bia epidemiologic\u0103 prin infec\u021bia COVID-19, 2 aprilie, ora 17.30 |trans-title=The epidemiological situation related to COVID-19 infection, 2 April, 17:30 |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/situatia-epidemiologica-prin-infectia-covid-19-2-aprilie-ora-1730 |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection of the Republic of Moldova |accessdate=12 April 2020 |language=ro |date=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics==\n{{Graph:Chart\n| type = line\n| linewidth = 1\n| showSymbols = 1\n| width = 700\n| height = 200\n| colors = #FF6347, #FFC000, #87CEEB, #343132\n| showValues =\n| xAxisTitle = Date\n| xAxisAngle = -60\n\n| x = 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr, 7 Apr, 8 Apr, 9 Apr, 10 Apr, 11 Apr, 12 Apr, 13 Apr, 14 Apr, 15 Apr, 16 Apr, 17 Apr, 18 Apr, 19 Apr\n\n| yAxisTitle = Total No. of cases\n| legend = Legend\n\n| y1Title = Confirmed\n| y1 = 1