{"title_page": "1893 Penn State Nittany Lions football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year=1893\n  |team=Penn State Nittany Lions\n  |sport=football\n  |image=Penn State Football 1893.jpg\n  |image_size=200px\n  |conference=Independent\n  |record=4\u20131\n  |conf_record=\n  |head_coach=[[George Hoskins (coach)|George Hoskins]]\n  |hc_year=2nd\n  |off_scheme=\n  |def_scheme=\n  |stadium=Beaver Field\n  |champion=\n}}\n{{1893 Eastern college football independents records}}\nThe '''1893 Penn State Nittany Lions football team''' represented the [[Pennsylvania State University]] in the [[1893 college football season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Penn State Yearly Results (1890-1894)|publisher=David DeLassus|work=College Football Data Warehouse|accessdate=August 9, 2015|url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/p/penn_state/1890-1894_yearly_results.php}}</ref> The team was coached by [[George Hoskins (coach)|George Hoskins]].  It was first team to play on Beaver Field, Penn State football's first permanent home.\n\nDespite the article title, the school did not adopt the [[Nittany Lion]] as its mascot until 1907.\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1893\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Eastern\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 14\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1893 Virginia Cavaliers football team|Virginia]]\n| site_stadium = Madison Hall Field\n| site_cityst = [[Charlottesville, VA]]\n| score = 6\u20130\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 25\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1893 Penn Quakers football team|Penn]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Philadelphia, PA]]\n| score = 6\u201318\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 6\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1893|team=Pittsburgh Panthers|title=Pittsburgh}}\n| gamename = [[Penn State\u2013Pittsburgh football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| site_stadium = Beaver Field\n| site_cityst = [[State College, PA]]