{"title_page": "Tessa Violet", "text_new": "{{short description|American singer-songwriter and video blogger}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                 = Tessa Violet\n| image                = Tessa Violet September 2018.png\n| alt                  =\n| caption              = Violet in September 2018\n| birth_name           = Tessa Violet Williams\n| birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1990|03|20}}\n| birth_place          = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S.\n| years_active         = 2013\u2013present\n| occupation           = Singer-songwriter, video blogger\n| instruments          = {{flatlist|\n*Vocals\n*guitar\n*piano\n*ukelele\n}}\n| genre                = [[Indie pop]]\n| associated_acts      = {{hlist|People You Know|Rusty Clanton|[[Dodie Clark]]|[[Bry (singer)|Bry]]|Shawna Howson}}\n* [[Orla Gartland]]\n* [[Lauren Aquilina]]\n*[[Leadley]]\n* Jon Cozart\n| label                = T\u2206G MUSIC\n| module               = {{Infobox person|child=yes\n| home_town            = [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]], [[Oregon]], United States}}\n| website              = https://tessa-violet.com\n| background           = solo_singer\n| module2              = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_direct_url   = channel/UCOw4v1j3QnzH7X4krQAS7fg\n| channel_display_name = Tessa Violet\n| pseudonym            = Meekakitty\n| genre                = {{hlist|Music|[[vlogging]]}}\n| subscribers          = 1,550,633 subscribers\n|views                = 77,022,481 (March 20, 2019)\n| silver_button        = yes\n| silver_year          =\n| gold_button          = yes\n| gold_year            =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Tessa Violet Williams''' (born March 20, 1990), better known as '''Tessa Violet''' and previously known as '''Meekakitty''', is a singer-songwriter and [[Video blogging|video blogger]] from the United States. Creator of the official quarantine anthem Bored, from her latest album Bad Ideas.\n\n==Early life and career==\nViolet grew up in [[Ashland, Oregon]]. She performed in theatre productions while in high school.\n\nViolet began daily vlogging in 2007 for a school project<ref name=\"nypost\">{{cite web|last=Cohen|first=Stefanie|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/cashin_in_on_video_6jtumyq5sPP1veR1iOoPJL|title=Cashin' in on video|work=[[New York Post]]|date=July 25, 2010|accessdate=July 2, 2011}}</ref> under the username Meekakitty when working in [[Hong Kong]] and [[Thailand]] as a fashion model. However, she quit modelling by 2009. Violet's early content focused on storytelling, skits, and music videos, including fan-made music videos for popular artists such as [[Relient K]], [[Family Force 5]], and [[Mika (singer)|Mika]].\n\nAfter moving to [[New York City]] in 2009, Violet gained attention after winning $100,000 in a YouTube competition by receiving the most comments on her video entry.<ref name=\"nypost\" /><ref name=prnewswire>{{cite web|title=19-Year-Old YouTube Vlogger Receives Over One Million Views and Wins $100,000 in Lashes to Riches Giveaway|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/19-year-old-youtube-vlogger-receives-over-one-million-views-and-wins-100000-in-lashes-to-riches-giveaway-80689912.html|publisher=[[PR Newswire]] / Beauty Biosciences|accessdate=July 2, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Violet was featured in fellow YouTube creator Nanalew's music video for the song \"[[Sail (song)|Sail]]\" by [[Awolnation]]. The video went viral and has since amassed over 310 million views. On September 24, 2012, Violet appeared in the music video for \"Cray Button\" by [[Family Force 5]].<ref name=\"breathe\">{{cite web|url=http://breathecast.christianpost.com/articles/4692/20120925/family-force-5-lecrae-cray-button-video-news-christian.htm|title=Family Force 5 Hits the \"Cray Button\" with new Video Premiere Featuring Lecrae|date=September 25, 2012|publisher=[[The Christian Post Company]]|format=Web|work=Breathecast|author=Merge PR|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130119145454/http://breathecast.christianpost.com/articles/4692/20120925/family-force-5-lecrae-cray-button-video-news-christian.htm|archivedate=January 19, 2013}}</ref> She also directed the music video for the group's song \"Chainsaw\", featuring [[Tedashii]].\n\nSince beginning to record and release music in 2013, the focus of Violet's channel has shifted to her original music. She has also dropped the moniker ''Meekakitty'', instead using her real name, Tessa Violet, across all platforms. It later became an official music channel in 2019.\n\n==Music==\nViolet released her<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/maybe-trapped-mostly-troubled-mw0002653423/credits|title=Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled|publisher=All Music|accessdate=December 8, 2016}}</ref> first album ''[[Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled]]'' on March 18, 2014. The album was produced by Seth Earnest at [[Maker Studios]], with John Zappin as A&R.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/maybe-trapped-mostly-troubled-mw0002653423/ |title=Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled |publisher=All Music |access-date=June 15, 2015}}</ref> Despite the lack of attention from traditional media sources, the record debuted at number 10 on the [[Billboard Heatseekers]] chart and sold 5,000 copies in the first three months.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=meekakitty|author=Tessa Violet|number=449287894075998208|date=March 27, 2014|title=My album is #10 on @billboard 's Heatseekers chart!!}}</ref>\n\nViolet released the lead single \"Dream\" from her EP ''[[Halloway (EP)|Halloway]]'' on September 16, 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=Tessa Violet|title=Tessa Violet - Dream (official music video)|date=September 16, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-4NLarMj4xU|accessdate=September 27, 2016}}</ref> The full EP was released October 14, 2016. She released videos for all songs on the project.<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Tessa-Violet-Halloway/release/9060210</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Violet revealed she was working on her second album, ''Bad Ideas''.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G2aBXLbz_jM&t=315s\n|title=a year of bad ideas|last=Violet|first=Tessa|date=April 22, 2018|website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> \"Crush,\" the first single from the record, was released June 15, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aje3LK9reQU|title=crush teaser|via=YouTube}}</ref> An accompanying music video directed by Big Forest was released on YouTube on the same day.<ref name=\"twitter.com\">https://twitter.com/TessaViolet/status/1007720726525140992</ref> As of March 2020, the music video has reached over 58 million views. The single led to Violet being featured on YouTube's Artist On The Rise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SiAuAJBZuGs|title=Tessa Violet - Crush (Official Music Video)|via=YouTube}}</ref> The entire album was set to release on August 3, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url= https://indiepulsemusic.com/2018/06/19/tessa-violet-crush/|title=Tessa Violet Announces New Album, Bad Ideas To Be Released August 3rd.|last=Timmons|first=Joseph|date=June 19, 2018|website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> before an alteration in the album's release plan. The album's title track, \"Bad Ideas,\" was released as a single on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TessaViolet/status/1068372110739832832|title=BAD IDEAS OUT NOW @spotify : https://spoti.fi/2E4wBBi @AppleMusic : https://apple.co/2E2Di73 pic.twitter.com/XwaM5eppOm|first=Tessa|last=Violet|date=November 29, 2018}}</ref> \"I Like (the idea of) You\" came out in May 2019. <ref>http://www.mtv.com/news/3122895/tessa-violet-i-like-the-idea-of-you-interview/</ref> She released ''Bad Ideas Act One EP'' in July 2019, featuring remixes of the first three singles of the project.<ref>https://www.lofficielusa.com/music/tessa-violet-remixes-2019</ref>\n\nOn October 25, Violet released her second album ''Bad Ideas.'' The album contains 11 tracks, 4 of which have been released as singles (''Crush'', ''Bad'' ''Ideas'', ''I Like (the idea of) You'', and ''Games''). The song was released via the label ''T\u2206G MUSIC''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://floodmagazine.com/70590/premiere-tessa-violet-knows-words-aint-enough-on-her-second-albums-lead-single/|title=Bad Ideas}}</ref> \n\nViolet has also been involved in numerous musical collaborations. In December 2014, Violet teamed with fellow YouTube musician Rusty Clanton to form the band People You Know. The pair released a Christmas album called ''You, Me and Christmas'', featuring four cover songs and one original song entitled \"You and Christmas.\" She has also collaborated with [[Dodie Clark]], [[Lauren Aquilina]], [[Orla Gartland]] and [[Bry (singer)|Bry]].\n\nViolet cites artists such as [[Lorde]], [[Bleachers (band)|Bleachers]], [[Lily Allen]], [[Taylor Swift]], [[Cavetown (musician)|cavetown]], and [[Julia Michaels]] among her influences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thefullest.com/2018/08/07/why-were-infatuated-with-tessa-violet/|title=Why We're Infatuated with Tessa Violet|date=August 7, 2018|website=The Fullest}}</ref>\n\n==Internet meme==\nAt the beginning of 2019, Tessa Violet became a meme among [[Russian nationalists|Russian nationalists]] who began to publish photos and videos of the singer with the words \u201cLet's Go Russians!\u201d and jokingly proclaimed Tessa \"Queen of the Russian state\".<ref>https://lenta.ru/news/2019/01/16/russianqueen/</ref> This culminated in a small group of Russian nationalists yelling \"Let's Go Russians\" during Violet's performance in Moscow in October 2019.<ref>https://memepedia.ru/tessa-vajolet-russkie-vpered-na-koncerte-v-moskve/</ref>\n\n==Film==\nViolet played the role of Tricia in the 2016 independent film ''[[The Matchbreaker]]''. Her song \"Cash Cash Money\" was included on the film's soundtrack.\n\n==Discography==\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = studio\n| Name = [[Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled]]\n| Released = 2014\n| Label = Maker Music}}\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = EP\n| Name = [[Halloway (EP)|Halloway]]\n| Released = 2016\n| Label = Independent\n| Producer = Seth Earnest\n| Singles = Dream}}\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = album\n| Name = Bad Ideas\n| Released = October 25, 2019\n| Label = T\u2206G MUSIC\n| Singles = Crush, Bad Ideas, I Like (the Idea of) You, Games}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Violet, Tessa}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:American comedy musicians]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in Canada]]\n[[Category:American female guitarists]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American folk guitarists]]\n[[Category:American indie pop musicians]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Female YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Maker Studios people]]\n[[Category:Music YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Nerd culture]]\n[[Category:People from Ashland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Science fiction fans]]\n[[Category:Singers from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Singers from Oregon]]\n[[Category:Video bloggers]]\n[[Category:Women bloggers]]\n[[Category:Women video bloggers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American singer-songwriter and video blogger}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                 = Tessa Violet\n| image                = Tessa Violet September 2018.png\n| alt                  =\n| caption              = Violet in September 2018\n| birth_name           = Tessa Violet Williams\n| birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1990|03|20}}\n| birth_place          = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S.\n| years_active         = 2013\u2013present\n| occupation           = Singer-songwriter, video blogger\n| instruments          = {{flatlist|\n*Vocals\n*guitar\n*piano\n*ukelele\n}}\n| genre                = [[Indie pop]]\n| associated_acts      = {{hlist|People You Know|Rusty Clanton|[[Dodie Clark]]|[[Bry (singer)|Bry]]|Shawna Howson}}\n* [[Orla Gartland]]\n* [[Lauren Aquilina]]\n*[[Leadley]]\n* Jon Cozart\n| label                = T\u2206G MUSIC\n| module               = {{Infobox person|child=yes\n| home_town            = [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland]], [[Oregon]], United States}}\n| website              = https://tessa-violet.com\n| background           = solo_singer\n| module2              = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_direct_url   = channel/UCOw4v1j3QnzH7X4krQAS7fg\n| channel_display_name = Tessa Violet\n| pseudonym            = Meekakitty\n| genre                = {{hlist|Music|[[vlogging]]}}\n| subscribers          = 1,550,633 subscribers\n|views                = 77,022,481 (March 20, 2019)\n| silver_button        = yes\n| silver_year          =\n| gold_button          = yes\n| gold_year            =\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Tessa Violet Williams''' (born March 20, 1990), better known as '''Tessa Violet''' and previously known as '''Meekakitty''', is a singer-songwriter and [[Video blogging|video blogger]] from the United States. Creator of the official quarantine anthem Bored, from her latest album Bad Ideas.\n\n==Early life and career==\nViolet grew up in [[Ashland, Oregon]]. She performed in theatre productions while in high school.\n\nViolet began daily vlogging in 2007 for a school project<ref name=\"nypost\">{{cite web|last=Cohen|first=Stefanie|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/cashin_in_on_video_6jtumyq5sPP1veR1iOoPJL|title=Cashin' in on video|work=[[New York Post]]|date=July 25, 2010|accessdate=July 2, 2011}}</ref> under the username Meekakitty when working in [[Hong Kong]] and [[Thailand]] as a fashion model. However, she quit modelling by 2009. Violet's early content focused on storytelling, skits, and music videos, including fan-made music videos for popular artists such as [[Relient K]], [[Family Force 5]], and [[Mika (singer)|Mika]].\n\nAfter moving to [[New York City]] in 2009, Violet gained attention after winning $100,000 in a YouTube competition by receiving the most comments on her video entry.<ref name=\"nypost\" /><ref name=prnewswire>{{cite web|title=19-Year-Old YouTube Vlogger Receives Over One Million Views and Wins $100,000 in Lashes to Riches Giveaway|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/19-year-old-youtube-vlogger-receives-over-one-million-views-and-wins-100000-in-lashes-to-riches-giveaway-80689912.html|publisher=[[PR Newswire]] / Beauty Biosciences|accessdate=July 2, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Violet was featured in fellow YouTube creator Nanalew's music video for the song \"[[Sail (song)|Sail]]\" by [[Awolnation]]. The video went viral and has since amassed over 310 million views. On September 24, 2012, Violet appeared in the music video for \"Cray Button\" by [[Family Force 5]].<ref name=\"breathe\">{{cite web|url=http://breathecast.christianpost.com/articles/4692/20120925/family-force-5-lecrae-cray-button-video-news-christian.htm|title=Family Force 5 Hits the \"Cray Button\" with new Video Premiere Featuring Lecrae|date=September 25, 2012|publisher=[[The Christian Post Company]]|format=Web|work=Breathecast|author=Merge PR|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130119145454/http://breathecast.christianpost.com/articles/4692/20120925/family-force-5-lecrae-cray-button-video-news-christian.htm|archivedate=January 19, 2013}}</ref> She also directed the music video for the group's song \"Chainsaw\", featuring [[Tedashii]].\n\nSince beginning to record and release music in 2013, the focus of Violet's channel has shifted to her original music. She has also dropped the moniker ''Meekakitty'', instead using her real name, Tessa Violet, across all platforms. It later became an official music channel in 2019.\n\n==Music==\nViolet released her<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/maybe-trapped-mostly-troubled-mw0002653423/credits|title=Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled|publisher=All Music|accessdate=December 8, 2016}}</ref> first album ''[[Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled]]'' on March 18, 2014. The album was produced by Seth Earnest at [[Maker Studios]], with John Zappin as A&R.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/maybe-trapped-mostly-troubled-mw0002653423/ |title=Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled |publisher=All Music |access-date=June 15, 2015}}</ref> Despite the lack of attention from traditional media sources, the record debuted at number 10 on the [[Billboard Heatseekers]] chart and sold 5,000 copies in the first three months.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=meekakitty|author=Tessa Violet|number=449287894075998208|date=March 27, 2014|title=My album is #10 on @billboard 's Heatseekers chart!!}}</ref>\n\nViolet released the lead single \"Dream\" from her EP ''Halloway'' on September 16, 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=Tessa Violet|title=Tessa Violet - Dream (official music video)|date=September 16, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-4NLarMj4xU|accessdate=September 27, 2016}}</ref> The full EP was released October 14, 2016. She released videos for all songs on the project.<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Tessa-Violet-Halloway/release/9060210</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Violet revealed she was working on her second album, ''Bad Ideas''.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G2aBXLbz_jM&t=315s\n|title=a year of bad ideas|last=Violet|first=Tessa|date=April 22, 2018|website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> \"Crush,\" the first single from the record, was released June 15, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aje3LK9reQU|title=crush teaser|via=YouTube}}</ref> An accompanying music video directed by Big Forest was released on YouTube on the same day.<ref name=\"twitter.com\">https://twitter.com/TessaViolet/status/1007720726525140992</ref> As of March 2020, the music video has reached over 58 million views. The single led to Violet being featured on YouTube's Artist On The Rise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SiAuAJBZuGs|title=Tessa Violet - Crush (Official Music Video)|via=YouTube}}</ref> The entire album was set to release on August 3, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url= https://indiepulsemusic.com/2018/06/19/tessa-violet-crush/|title=Tessa Violet Announces New Album, Bad Ideas To Be Released August 3rd.|last=Timmons|first=Joseph|date=June 19, 2018|website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> before an alteration in the album's release plan. The album's title track, \"Bad Ideas,\" was released as a single on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TessaViolet/status/1068372110739832832|title=BAD IDEAS OUT NOW @spotify : https://spoti.fi/2E4wBBi @AppleMusic : https://apple.co/2E2Di73 pic.twitter.com/XwaM5eppOm|first=Tessa|last=Violet|date=November 29, 2018}}</ref> \"I Like (the idea of) You\" came out in May 2019. <ref>http://www.mtv.com/news/3122895/tessa-violet-i-like-the-idea-of-you-interview/</ref> She released ''Bad Ideas Act One EP'' in July 2019, featuring remixes of the first three singles of the project.<ref>https://www.lofficielusa.com/music/tessa-violet-remixes-2019</ref>\n\nOn October 25, Violet released her second album ''Bad Ideas.'' The album contains 11 tracks, 4 of which have been released as singles (''Crush'', ''Bad'' ''Ideas'', ''I Like (the idea of) You'', and ''Games''). The song was released via the label ''T\u2206G MUSIC''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://floodmagazine.com/70590/premiere-tessa-violet-knows-words-aint-enough-on-her-second-albums-lead-single/|title=Bad Ideas}}</ref> \n\nViolet has also been involved in numerous musical collaborations. In December 2014, Violet teamed with fellow YouTube musician Rusty Clanton to form the band People You Know. The pair released a Christmas album called ''You, Me and Christmas'', featuring four cover songs and one original song entitled \"You and Christmas.\" She has also collaborated with [[Dodie Clark]], [[Lauren Aquilina]], [[Orla Gartland]] and [[Bry (singer)|Bry]].\n\nViolet cites artists such as [[Lorde]], [[Bleachers (band)|Bleachers]], [[Lily Allen]], [[Taylor Swift]], [[Cavetown (musician)|cavetown]], and [[Julia Michaels]] among her influences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thefullest.com/2018/08/07/why-were-infatuated-with-tessa-violet/|title=Why We're Infatuated with Tessa Violet|date=August 7, 2018|website=The Fullest}}</ref>\n\n==Internet meme==\nAt the beginning of 2019, Tessa Violet became a meme among [[Russian nationalists|Russian nationalists]] who began to publish photos and videos of the singer with the words \u201cLet's Go Russians!\u201d and jokingly proclaimed Tessa \"Queen of the Russian state\".<ref>https://lenta.ru/news/2019/01/16/russianqueen/</ref> This culminated in a small group of Russian nationalists yelling \"Let's Go Russians\" during Violet's performance in Moscow in October 2019.<ref>https://memepedia.ru/tessa-vajolet-russkie-vpered-na-koncerte-v-moskve/</ref>\n\n==Film==\nViolet played the role of Tricia in the 2016 independent film ''[[The Matchbreaker]]''. Her song \"Cash Cash Money\" was included on the film's soundtrack.\n\n==Discography==\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = studio\n| Name = [[Maybe Trapped Mostly Troubled]]\n| Released = 2014\n| Label = Maker Music}}\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = EP\n| Name = Halloway\n| Released = 2016\n| Label = Independent\n| Producer = Seth Earnest\n| Singles = Dream}}\n\n{{Discography list\n| Type = album\n| Name = Bad Ideas\n| Released = October 25, 2019\n| Label = T\u2206G MUSIC\n| Singles = Crush, Bad Ideas, I Like (the Idea of) You, Games}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Violet, Tessa}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:American comedy musicians]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in Canada]]\n[[Category:American female guitarists]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American folk guitarists]]\n[[Category:American indie pop musicians]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Female YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Maker Studios people]]\n[[Category:Music YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Nerd culture]]\n[[Category:People from Ashland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Science fiction fans]]\n[[Category:Singers from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Singers from Oregon]]\n[[Category:Video bloggers]]\n[[Category:Women bloggers]]\n[[Category:Women video bloggers]]\n", "name_user": "DoctorWho42", "label": "safe", "comment": "Linking toHalloway (EP)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tessa_Violet"}
